Peter,
very interesting.
thanks for sharing.

IMO a better experiment would be to eliminate the goal(red dot) while training the bot.
Naturally, you need some sort of intermediate goal to do anything useful.
set the goal as mapping the maze instead of finding the red dot.
Now, you have another very acceptable &quot;gimmee&quot; behavior to add to the bot.
pick a wall(right or left) and follow it until you get back to where you started.
then do the same thing with the other wall.
now put the red dot back in anywhere you want.

the bot now sees the forest in spite of the trees.




